<p class="EnTeteTranscription">Cameron, Duncan. A Sketch of the Nipigon Country with extracts from His Journal, 1804. An electronic transcription. MFTP #0025</p><div class="ContenuPage">
<p style="text-align:justify;">3<sup>rd</sup> September<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  I began to make the Outfit for <span class="Gap">[&#8230;]</span> which I gave in Charge to Rejiste Bellefleure, <span class="Gap">[&#8230;]</span> m<span class="AddHand-editors">[uch]</span> <span class="AddHand-editors">[a]</span>gainst his will, as his pride was very much hurt by the Osnaburgh Chief, who would <span class="AddHand-author">not</span> acknowledge him to be a great Man, and those Canadians whom we rise from an Inferior Station, to a higher One, are Just as Vain of being reckon'd great Men as the Indians themselves are, but very Seldom pursue th<span class="AddHand-editors">[e]</span> proper Manner to become Consequential, for Vanity, Selfishness, or Drunkeness, soon Spoils the most part of them<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  <span class="AddHand-editors">[H]</span>owever, I had no One Else to leave, Except M<sup>r</sup> Cameron, who, I wanted very much Else where, as will Appear here after<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  I gave him four good Men, of which Michél Forçier <span class="AddHand-editors">[is]</span> One, to be an Assistant to him, as he is the Ablest Ma<span class="AddHand-editors">[n]</span> for that purpose of any in the Brigade<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  I was greatl<span class="AddHand-editors">[y]</span> troubled with the Indians all Day, who had now m<span class="AddHand-editors">[ore]</span> things to Say, that they Could not Yesterday, while they were Sober, besides repeating what they had already sa<span class="AddHand-editors">[id]</span> at least Twenty times Over<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  <span class="AddHand-editors">[H]</span>owever, I got the Outfit Completed inspite of them, and Our Bales made up agai<span class="AddHand-editors">[n,]</span> after which, I Aranged the Loading, and Men, of the <span class="AddHand-editors">[Ca]</span>noes, and gave the Guide Orders to Set off to<span class="AddHand-editors">[morrow]</span> morning with the Brigade<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span></p>

<p align="page-number"><span class="AddHand-editors">[62]</span></p>

